Course Objectives

  • This course offers a comprehensive introduction of test automation for web applications using Selenium and Cucumber.
  • The course starts with an end­-to-­end tutorial for writing tests using Selenium and Cucumber, with an emphasis on maintainability and best practices throughot.
  • Optional modules provide for a customized in­depth discussion of specific advanced Selenium features and practices used by teams to further automate testing in a continuous integration environment.
  • By the end of this course, you will be able to …
    • Rapidly create initial test scripts using Selenium Builder.
    • Navigate the WebDriver API and online documentation, and identify relevant parts necessary to perform key tasks.
    • Maintain, debug and modify Selenium test scripts using the Selenium API.
    • Communicate using the core vocabulary and concepts essential to testing with Selenium.
    • Use Selenium Selectors to interact with and verify content in web pages.
    • Refactor scripts for maintainability using the Page Object design pattern.
    • Integrate tests with Cucumber to achieve Behavior Driven / Acceptance Test Driven Development (BDD/ATDD).

Course Audience

  • This course targets QA and Test Automation engineers with programming experience seeking to learn the fundamentals of test automation using Cucumber and Selenium.
  • This course may also be of interest to engineers and team leads seeking best practices for designing and configuring a test automation environment.

Setup Lab A - Install Firebug and Firepath plugins for Firefox

  1. Open Firefox Add-ons page in Firefox browser, e.g. https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/extensions

  2. Search for Firebug extension, e.g. https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/search/?q=firebug

  3. Next to Firebug extension, click on Add to Firefox

  4. You will be asked to install add-on Firebug (Author not verified), click on Install Now

  5. Search for Firepath extension, e.g. https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/search/?q=firepath

  6. Next to Firepath extension, click on Add to Firefox

  7. You will be asked to install add-on Firepath (Author not verified), click on Install Now

  8. You will be asked to restart Firefox, click on Restart now

Setup Lab B - Install Selenium Builder plugin for Firefox

  1. Download Selenium Builder from http://seleniumbuilder.github.io/se-builder/

  2. The downloaded file is selenium-builder-latest-sauce.xpi

  3. Open Firefox and open downloaded file from Firefox (drag-and-drop works too)

  4. You will be asked to install add-on Selenium Builder (Author not verified), click on Install Now

  5. You will be asked to restart Firefox, click on Restart now.

Setup Lab C - Run Smoke Test

  1. Download selenium-smoke-test Maven project, e.g. selenium-smoke-test.zip

  2. Alternatively, you can import Maven project from Github repository, e.g. https://github.com/javaclinic/selenium-smoke-test.git

  3. Open Eclipse

  4. If using downloaded version, please unpack ZIP archive to Eclipse workspace

  5. Import selenium-smoke-test project as a Maven project

  6. Alternatively, use Import feature and select Git --> Projects from Git feature

  7. Once created execute two test cases, e.g.

    1. In src/test/java run com.example.calculator.RunCukesTest as a Java JUnit test case

    2. In src/test/java run com.example.shopping.RunSeleniumSmokeTest as a JUnit test case

  8. Observe that the test successfully passed.

Introduction to Automated Web Testing

What is Automated Web Testing?

  • Using a software tool to run repeatable tests against the web application
  • Automated Web Testing
    • Automated
    • Software Testing
    • Focused on web applications

Why is Web Testing Automation important?

  • Web applications - most common software applications
  • We want to automate tedious tasks of testing web applications:
    • using different browsers
    • on various platforms
  • Resources required for a large/dedicated test team
    • People
    • Time
    • Money
  • Modern software development practices require test automation
    • Repeatability (regression testing)
    • Speed (rapid feedback)
    • Disciplined documentation of test cases

Software Testing

  • Testing Types

Introduction to Selenium

What is Selenium?

  • Suite of software tools to automate web browsers across many platforms
  • Ensures that web application works and will continue working across a set of supported browsers/platforms
  • Runs in many browsers
    • Firefox (latest release) - e.g. Selenium 2.40.0 supports Firefox 27, 26, 24, 17
    • Internet Explorer - versions 6, 7, 8, 9, 10 and 11 (requires additional configuration)
    • Safari, e.g. Safari 5.1+ (only on OSX)
    • Opera, e.g. Opera 12.x and older versions
    • Chromium (Chrome)
  • Runs on many operating systems
    • Microsoft Windows (Windows XP, Windows 7, Windows 8, Windows 8.1)
    • Apple OS X
    • Linux
  • Can be controlled by many programming langauges and testing frameworks
    • Java with JUnit and TestNG
    • Ruby with RSpec and Test::Unit
    • Python with unittest, pyunit, py.test, robot framework
    • C# with NUnit
  • Open source - Apache Licence

Selenium Purpose

  • Selenium is typically used for rapid development of test automation for web applications, across browsers and operating system platforms.
  • Could be used for other automation web tasks, e.g. web administration tasks automation.

Selenium History

  • HP Mercury Tools (QTP) is dominating/poisoning the market,
    • The cure is to take Selenium supplements
  • In 2004 - Jason Huggins at Thoughtworks developed *JavaScriptTestRunner for internal timesheet application
    • Selenium 1 - Selenium Remote Controller (Selenium RC)
    • Uses generic JavaScript (Selenium Core) that drive the web application on a browser
    • Same-Origin Policy - can’t execute JavaScript from different domain
    • Cross-site Scripting
    • Selenium RC acts as a HTTP Proxy Server
  • In 2006 - Simon Stewart at Google started WebDriver project
    • Addresses Selenium RC (Selenium 1) issues
    • Implements browser-specific implementations
    • Adheres more closely to OOP fundamentals
  • In 2008 - Selenium 1 and WebDriver merged
  • More details
    • http://docs.seleniumhq.org/about/history.jsp

Selenium RC vs Selenium WebDriver

  • Browser handling
    • Selenium RC drives the browser through Selenium Core (JavaScript)
    • Selenium RC limted to JavaScript sandbox of the browser
    • Selenium RC might not work well across different browsers (different JavaScript engines)
    • Selenium WebDriver speaks to browser natively
  • Better APIs
    • Selenium WebDriver has a very good set of APIs
    • Selenium WebDriver follows good OOP practices
  • Mobile Application testing
    • Selenium WebDriver has mobile-specific implementations, e.g. AndroidDriver and IPhoneDriver
  • Large user/developer community, active development, support
    • Selenium RC (Selenium 1) is deprecated and in maintenance mode only
    • Selenium WebDriver (Selenium 2) is newer and being actively developed

Selenium Components

  • Web Application Under Test (WAUT)
  • Selenium 1
    • Selenium Core
    • Selenium IDE
    • Selenium RC (Remote Control)
  • Selenium 2
    • Selenium WebDriver implementations
      • FirefoxDriver
      • SafariDriver
      • ChromeDriver
      • InternetExplorerDriver
      • OperaDriver
      • AndroidDriver
      • IPhoneDriver
    • Selenium Grid
    • Selenium Builder
  • Selenese

Selenium 1 Architecture

Selenium 2 Architecture

Selenium Core

  • Core JavaScript library developed by Jason Huggins and ThoughtWorks
  • Foundation for other components Selenium IDE and Selenium RC

Selenium IDE

  • Integrated Development Environment (IDE)
  • Prototyping tool
  • Runs as plugin/extension for Firefox
  • Records and playbacks actions and interactions with the browser
  • Creates and edits test cases and suites
  • Converts test cases to different languages
  • Download
    • http://release.seleniumhq.org/selenium-ide/

Selenium Builder

  • Similar IDE tool
  • Rapid development of Selenium scripts
  • Runs as plugin/extension for Firefox
  • Records and playbacks actions and interactions with the browser
    • Local playback
    • Remote webdriver playback
  • Supports Selenium 1 and Selenium 2
  • Creates and edits test cases and suites
    • uses Selenium IDE format (HTML table) to store/load scripts
    • uses JSON format to store/load scripts
  • Exports test cases to different languages
  • Integration with Github
  • Download
    • https://seleniumbuilder.github.io/se-builder/
    • https://saucelabs.com/builder

Selenese

  • Selenium commands that run tests
  • Command types
    • Actions
    • Accessors
    • Assertions
    • Element Locators
    • Patterns
  • Will discuss these in detail later

Introduction to Selenium Builder

What is Selenium Builder?

  • Development tool for Selenium scripts
  • Records and playbacks actions and interactions with the browser
  • Can create tests cases and test suites
  • Can export test cases to different languages and frameworks
    • Java JUnit, Java TestNG, Ruby, Python, etc.
  • Integration with Github

How do I install Selenium Builder?

  • Open Firefox to http://sebuilder.com
  • Click on Install button
    • http://seleniumbuilder.github.io/se-builder/selenium-builder-latest.xpi
  • Allow for Firefox extension to be installed, e.g. click on Allow
  • Restart Firefox

Lab 01 - Explore Selenium Builder

  1. Open Shopping page in Firefox, e.g. https://XXXX-YYYY-DDDD.spree.mx/

  2. If the shop does not exist, you can create one yourself by registering at http://spreecommerce.com

  3. Start Selenium Builder (Tools → Web Developer → Launch Selenium Builder)

  4. Click the SHOP link at the top of the page

  5. Click on the image of the Rails Tote Bag (1st product on the 1st row)

  6. Click on Add To Cart Button

  7. Click on Continue Shopping Button

  8. Click on Spree in Shop by Brand section

  9. Click on the Spree Ringer T Shirt image

  10. Click on Add To Cart Button

  11. Go back to Selenium Builder and click on Record a verification

  12. Click on the amount (recorded by Selenium Builder), i.e. verify that the total is $35.98

  13. Click on Continue Shopping

  14. Click on Ruby on Rails Tote Bag Image

  15. Click on Featured under LOOK FOR SIMILAR ITEMS

  16. Check box $15.00-$18.00 in PRICE RANGE section

  17. Click on Search button

  18. Click on Cart in top right corner

  19. Go back to Selenium Builder and click on Record a verification

  20. Click on the amount (recorded by Selenium Builder), i.e. verify that the total is $35.98

  21. Go back to Selenium Builder and click on Stop Recording

  22. Save the script in Selenium Builder, e.g. explore-selenium-builder.json

  23. Run the script locally, e.g. click on Run -> Run test locally

  24. Export the script as various source, e.g.

    • Java - ExploreSeleniumBuilderJava.java,
    • Java JUnit - ExploreSeleniumBuilderJavaJunit.java,
    • Java TestNG - ExploreSeleniumBuilderJavaTestng.java,
    • Ruby - ExploreSelemiumBuilderRuby.rb,
    • Python - ExploreSeleniumBuilderPython.py,
    • English - ExploreSeleniumBuilderEnglish.en.txt

  25. Explore the saved files.

  26. We won’t import this into Eclipse just yet.

require 'rubygems'
require 'selenium-webdriver'
wd = Selenium::WebDriver.for :firefox

wd.get "https://XXXX-YYYY-DDDD.spree.mx/"
wd.find_element(:css, "div.container > nav.columns.seven > #main-nav-bar > #shop-link > a > span.translation_missing").click
wd.find_element(:link_text, "Ruby on Rails Tote").click
wd.find_element(:id, "add-to-cart-button").click
wd.find_element(:link_text, "CONTINUE SHOPPING").click
wd.find_element(:xpath, "//aside[@id='sidebar']//a[.='Spree']").click
wd.find_element(:link_text, "Spree Ringer T-Shirt").click
wd.find_element(:id, "add-to-cart-button").click
if not wd.find_element(:tag_name, "html").text.include? "$35.98"
    print "verifyTextPresent failed"
end
wd.find_element(:link_text, "CONTINUE SHOPPING").click
wd.find_element(:link_text, "Ruby on Rails Tote").click
wd.find_element(:link_text, "Featured").click
if not wd.find_element(:id, "Price_Range_$15.00_-_$18.00").selected?
    wd.find_element(:id, "Price_Range_$15.00_-_$18.00").click
end
wd.find_element(:name, "button").click
wd.find_element(:css, "a.cart-info.full").click
if not wd.find_element(:tag_name, "html").text.include? "$35.98"
    print "verifyTextPresent failed"
end
wd.quit

(When you follow these steps, make sure page content is loaded before clicking, etc... Since you're a human, this is probably what you do already)

- Click the element on the page with the id of "add-to-cart-button"
- Click the link which says "CONTINUE SHOPPING"

- Click the link which says "Spree Ringer T-Shirt"

- Click the link which says "Ruby on Rails Tote"
- Click the link which says "Featured"

ExploreSeleniumBuilderJava.java
import java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;
import java.util.Date;
import java.io.File;
import org.openqa.selenium.support.ui.Select;
import org.openqa.selenium.interactions.Actions;
import org.openqa.selenium.firefox.FirefoxDriver;
import org.openqa.selenium.*;
import static org.openqa.selenium.OutputType.*;

public class ExploreSeleniumBuilderJava {

    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
        FirefoxDriver wd;
        wd = new FirefoxDriver();
        wd.manage().timeouts().implicitlyWait(60, TimeUnit.SECONDS);
        wd.get("https://XXXX-YYYY-DDDD.spree.mx/");
        wd.findElement(By.cssSelector("div.container > nav.columns.seven > #main-nav-bar > #shop-link > a > span.translation_missing")).click();
        wd.findElement(By.linkText("Ruby on Rails Tote")).click();
        wd.findElement(By.id("add-to-cart-button")).click();
        wd.findElement(By.linkText("CONTINUE SHOPPING")).click();
        wd.findElement(By.xpath("//aside[@id='sidebar']//a[.='Spree']")).click();
        wd.findElement(By.linkText("Spree Ringer T-Shirt")).click();
        wd.findElement(By.id("add-to-cart-button")).click();
        if (!wd.findElement(By.tagName("html")).getText().contains("$35.98")) {
            System.out.println("verifyTextPresent failed");
        }
        wd.findElement(By.linkText("CONTINUE SHOPPING")).click();
        wd.findElement(By.linkText("Ruby on Rails Tote")).click();
        wd.findElement(By.linkText("Featured")).click();
        if (!wd.findElement(By.id("Price_Range_$15.00_-_$18.00")).isSelected()) {
            wd.findElement(By.id("Price_Range_$15.00_-_$18.00")).click();
        }
        wd.findElement(By.name("button")).click();
        wd.findElement(By.cssSelector("a.cart-info.full")).click();
        if (!wd.findElement(By.tagName("html")).getText().contains("$35.98")) {
            System.out.println("verifyTextPresent failed");
        }
        wd.quit();
    }

    public static boolean isAlertPresent(FirefoxDriver wd) {
        try {
            wd.switchTo().alert();
            return true;
        } catch (NoAlertPresentException e) {
            return false;
        }
    }

}

package com.example.selenium.lab02;

import java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;

import org.junit.After;
import org.junit.Before;
import org.junit.Test;

public class ShoppingCartTest {

    public void testShoppingCart() {
        browser.get("https://XXXX-YYYY-DDDD.spree.mx/");
        browser.findElement(By.cssSelector("div.container > nav.columns.seven > #main-nav-bar > #shop-link > a > span.translation_missing")).click();
        browser.findElement(By.linkText("Ruby on Rails Tote")).click();
        browser.findElement(By.id("add-to-cart-button")).click();
        browser.findElement(By.linkText("CONTINUE SHOPPING")).click();
        browser.findElement(By.xpath("//aside[@id='sidebar']//a[.='Spree']")).click();
        browser.findElement(By.linkText("Spree Ringer T-Shirt")).click();
        browser.findElement(By.id("add-to-cart-button")).click();
        if (!browser.findElement(By.tagName("html")).getText().contains("$35.98")) {
            System.out.println("verifyTextPresent failed");
        }
        browser.findElement(By.linkText("CONTINUE SHOPPING")).click();
        browser.findElement(By.linkText("Ruby on Rails Tote")).click();
        browser.findElement(By.linkText("Featured")).click();
        if (!browser.findElement(By.id("Price_Range_$15.00_-_$18.00")).isSelected()) {

Lab 03 - Explore Firefox WebDriver

  1. Copy the previous example (i.e. ShoppingCartTest) to a new class in package com.example.selenium.lab03, and rename to a new name, e.g. GoogleSearchTest.

  2. Rename the test method, e.g. testGoogle, remove all content from the method.

  3. Use code completion (CTRL-SPACE), whenever writing new code.

  4. Use navigate().to(address) instead of get(address) method.

  5. Let’s output some information about the existing page, e.g. 

    System.out.println("Page title:  " + browser.getTitle());
System.out.println("Current URL: " + browser.getCurrentUrl());

  6. Let’s type something in the input field. Open Google in a browser, right click on the input field, and inspect with Firebug.

  7. The following is the HTML code that Google renders: 

    <input

  8. There are few ways that we can reference this form field. Let’s use By.name(...) for finding the WebElement object, e.g. 

    queryField = browser.findElement(By.name("q"));

  9. Notice the queryField does not have a type, use QuickFix to add the object type.

  10. Let’s type something into form field, e.g. "Selenium". Use sendKeys(...) method.

  11. Submit the form, e.g. queryField.submit()

  12. Now, let’s have the program wait/sleep for the browser to come back, at most 10 seconds, e.g. 

    waitFor(3.0);

  13. Don’t worry about syntax error, we will fix that next. Press QuickFix and pick Create method waitFor(double), e.g. 

    private void waitFor(double seconds) {
    // TODO Auto-generated method stub
}

  14. Let’s use Thread.sleep(...) for now, e.g. 

    private void waitFor(double seconds) {
    long wait = (long) (1000.0 * seconds);
    Thread.sleep(wait);
}

  15. Notice sleep requires handling the InterruptedException, let’s surround with try-catch block, e.g. 

    private void waitFor(double seconds) {
    long wait = (long) (1000.0 * seconds);
    try {
        Thread.sleep(wait);
    } catch (InterruptedException e) {
        // TODO Auto-generated catch block
        e.printStackTrace();
    }
}

  16. Output the information again.

  17. Run the program.

    1. What did you observe?

    2. What was the page title before submit? What was the page title after the submit?

  18. What if our tests take longer than 3 seconds? What if tests take shorter than 3 seconds? We probably don’t want sleep in our programs, since that makes our tests brittle. Let’s make this method @Deprecated, e.g. 

    @Deprecated
public static void waitFor(double seconds) {
    long wait = (long) (1000.0 * seconds);
    try {
        Thread.sleep(wait);
    } catch (InterruptedException e) {
        e.printStackTrace();
    }
}

  19. Instead, let’s use WebDriver API to wait for browser to return, e.g. 

        // waitFor(3.0);
    wait = new WebDriverWait(browser, 10);
    wait.until(condition);

    Use QuickFix to add variable types.

  20. Let’s add new condition as ExpectedCondition<Boolean>, e.g. 

        WebDriverWait wait = new WebDriverWait(browser, 10);
    condition = new ExpectedCondition<T>() {
    };
    wait.until(condition);

    Ignore the errors for now. We will fix them in a moment.

  21. We expect a boolean variable back, let’s change the parameter T into Boolean. Also, the ExpectedCondition interface expects the implementation, let’s add unimplemented methods, e.g. 

        ExpectedCondition<Boolean> condition = new ExpectedCondition<Boolean>() {
        @Override
        public Boolean apply(WebDriver arg0) {
            // TODO Auto-generated method stub
            return null;
        }
    };

  22. Let’s implement this anonymous class method, e.g. 

        ExpectedCondition<Boolean> condition = new ExpectedCondition<Boolean>() {
        @Override
        public Boolean apply(WebDriver driver) {
            return driver.getTitle().toLowerCase().startsWith("selenium");
        }
    };

  23. Finally, let’s refactor this code into a method, e.g. 

    private void waitForTitleIgnoreCase() {
    WebDriverWait wait = new WebDriverWait(browser, 10);
    ExpectedCondition<Boolean> condition = new ExpectedCondition<Boolean>() {
        @Override
        public Boolean apply(WebDriver driver) {
            return driver.getTitle().toLowerCase().startsWith("selenium");
        }
    };
    wait.until(condition);
}

    The title string and wait period should not be hardcoded in the method. Refactor and update the method signature, e.g.

    private void waitForTitleIgnoreCase(final String expectedTitle, final long seconds) {
    WebDriverWait wait = new WebDriverWait(browser, seconds);
    ExpectedCondition<Boolean> condition = new ExpectedCondition<Boolean>() {
        @Override
        public Boolean apply(WebDriver driver) {
            return driver.getTitle().toLowerCase().startsWith(expectedTitle);
        }
    };
    wait.until(condition);
}

    Update the method call, e.g.

        waitForTitleIgnoreCase("selenium", 10);

  24. Run the program again.

  25. Since this is a JUnit test case, we probably don’t want to output the information, but rather make assertions and fail if the text is not as expected.

  26. Replace output information with assertions, e.g. 

    ...
        // assert the title
        Assert.assertEquals("Google", browser.getTitle());

        // output the information
        // System.out.println("Page title:  " + browser.getTitle());
        // System.out.println("Current URL: " + browser.getCurrentUrl());

...

        // assert the title again
        Assert.assertEquals("Selenium - Google Search", browser.getTitle());

        // output information again
        // System.out.println("Page title:  " + browser.getTitle());
        // System.out.println("Current URL: " + browser.getCurrentUrl());
...
    Please note that you need to import org.junit.Assert not deprecated junit.framework.Assert class.

  27. Functional interfaces could be simplified using Java 8 Lambda expressions, e.g. 

    public void waitForTitleIgnoreCaseJava8(final String expectedTitle, final long seconds) {
    WebDriverWait wait = new WebDriverWait(browser, seconds);
    ExpectedCondition<Boolean> condition = (WebDriver driver) -> driver.getTitle().toLowerCase().startsWith(expectedTitle);
    wait.until(condition);
}

  28. Run the program again.

GoogleSearchTest.java
package com.example.selenium.lab03;

import java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;

import org.junit.After;
import org.junit.Assert;
import org.junit.Before;
import org.junit.Test;
import org.openqa.selenium.By;
import org.openqa.selenium.NoAlertPresentException;
import org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver;
import org.openqa.selenium.WebElement;
import org.openqa.selenium.firefox.FirefoxDriver;
import org.openqa.selenium.support.ui.ExpectedCondition;
import org.openqa.selenium.support.ui.ExpectedConditions;
import org.openqa.selenium.support.ui.WebDriverWait;

public class GoogleSearchTest {

    private FirefoxDriver browser;

    @Before
    public void setUp() throws Exception {
        browser = new FirefoxDriver();
        browser.manage().timeouts().implicitlyWait(60, TimeUnit.SECONDS);
    }

    @Test
    public void testSearchingForSelenium() {

        // navigate to google page
        browser.navigate().to("https://www.google.com");

        // output information about page/url
        // System.out.println("Page title: " + browser.getTitle());
        // System.out.println("Current URL: " + browser.getCurrentUrl());

        // assert the title
        Assert.assertEquals("Google", browser.getTitle());

        // find input (query) field by name, e.g. "q"
        WebElement queryField = browser.findElement(By.name("q"));

        // write some text to the input field
        queryField.sendKeys("Selenium");

        // wait(or sleep) for 3.0 seconds
        // waitFor(3.0);

        // wait for 10.0 seconds - or return immediately if "selenium" is the
        // start of the title (ignore case)
        waitForTitleIgnoreCase("selenium", 10.0);

        // output information again
        // System.out.println("Page title:  " + browser.getTitle());
        // System.out.println("Current URL: " + browser.getCurrentUrl());

        // assert the title again
        Assert.assertEquals("Selenium - Google Search", browser.getTitle());

        // quit browser
        browser.quit();

    }

    public void waitForTitleContains(final String titleContains, final double seconds) {
        long milis = (long) (1000 * seconds);
        WebDriverWait wait = new WebDriverWait(browser, milis);
        wait.until(ExpectedConditions.titleContains(titleContains));
    }

    public void waitForTitleIgnoreCase(final String titleStartsWith, final double seconds) {
        long milis = (long) (1000 * seconds);
        WebDriverWait wait = new WebDriverWait(browser, milis);
        ExpectedCondition<Boolean> condition = new ExpectedCondition<Boolean>() {
            @Override
            public Boolean apply(WebDriver driver) {
                return driver.getTitle().toLowerCase().startsWith(titleStartsWith);
            }
        };
        wait.until(condition);
    }

    public void waitForTitleIgnoreCaseJava8(final String expectedTitle, final long seconds) {
        WebDriverWait wait = new WebDriverWait(browser, seconds);
        ExpectedCondition<Boolean> condition = (WebDriver driver) -> driver.getTitle().toLowerCase()
                .startsWith(expectedTitle);
        wait.until(condition);
    }

    @Deprecated
    public void waitFor(double seconds) {
        long wait = (long) (1000.0 * seconds);
        try {
            Thread.sleep(wait);
        } catch (InterruptedException e) {
            // TODO Auto-generated catch block
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }

    @After
    public void tearDown() {
        browser.quit();
    }

    public static boolean isAlertPresent(FirefoxDriver wd) {
        try {
            wd.switchTo().alert();
            return true;
        } catch (NoAlertPresentException e) {
            return false;
        }
    }

}

Locating Web Elements

Finder Methods

  • findElement(...)
    • no matches - throws exception org.openqa.selenium.NoSuchElementException
    • 1 match - returns WebElement instance
    • 2+ matches - returns the first matching WebElement instance
  • findElements(...)
    • no matches - returns empty List<WebElement>
    • 1 match - returns List<WebElement> with one matching element
    • 2+ matches - returns List<WebElement> with all matching elements

By Methods

  • Name
  • ID
  • TagName
  • Class
  • Link
  • CSS
  • XPath

Name

<input name="q" ... >

WebElement searchbox = browser.findElement(By.name("q"));
  • Works great when NAME attribute are present (and unique) on HTML elements
  • NAME attribute might not be available
  • NAME attribute might not be unique (it’s not enforced)
  • NAME attribute might be dynamically generated by the server

Id

<input id="lst-ib" ... >

WebElement searchbox = browser.findElement(By.id("lst-ib"));
  • Works great when ID attributes are present on HTML elements
  • ID attribute might not be available
  • ID attribute might not be unique (it’s not enforced)
  • ID attribute might be dynamically generated by the server

Tag Name

List<WebElement> buttons = browser.findElements(By.tagName("button"));
  • Finds web elements by the HTML tag name

Link

WebElement aboutGoogleLink = browser.findElement(By.linkText("About Google"));
aboutGoogleLink.click();

List<WebElement> googleLinks = browser.findElements(By.partialLinkText("Google"));
  • Finds web elements by the exact/partial text displayed in the link

(CSS) Class

<input class="gsfi" ... >

WebElement searchbox = browser.findElement(By.className("gsfi"));
  • Finds web elements by the CSS class name

CSS Selectors

WebElement searchButton = browser.findElement(By.cssSelector("#flrs>a[href='/intl/en/about.html']"));
  • Finds web elements by the CSS selectors
  • ID, e.g. 
    By.cssSelector("#some_id")
  • Child element (sub-element), e.g. 
    By.cssSelector(" li > a ")
  • Absolute CSS Selector path, e.g. 
    By.cssSelector("html>body>div>input")
  • Relative CSS Selector path, e.g. 
    By.cssSelector("input")
  • Few more examples, e.g. 
    By.cssSelector("button[name='clear'")
By.cssSelector("#clear")
By.cssSelector("button#clear")
By.cssSelector(".someclass")
By.cssSelector("input.email")
By.cssSelector("a:contains('some_text')")
By.cssSelector("a[href='/some_url']")
By.cssSelector("img[alt='Alternate Image Text']")
By.cssSelector("img[alt]")
By.cssSelector("img:not[alt]")
By.cssSelector("div#products:first-child")
...
  • See the attached cheatsheet, e.g.
    • https://www.simple-talk.com/dotnet/.net-framework/xpath,-css,-dom-and-selenium-the-rosetta-stone/
  • See more examples, e.g.
    • http://www.w3schools.com/cssref/css_selectors.asp

XPath

WebElement element = browser.findElement(By.xpath("//*[@id='gbqfba']");
  • Uses XML Path (XPath) to find elements in HTML code
  • The root element is identified by /
  • Match any element is identified by //
  • Select the current node is identified by .
  • Select the parent node is identified by ..
  • Attributes are identified by @
  • Generic wildcard is identified by *
  • Attribute wildcard is identified by @*
  • Then you stack the XML elements, e.g.
    • //div - finds all <div> elements
    • //div/a - finds <a> (anchor/link) element under <div> element
    • //div/* - finds all elements under <div> element
    • //*/*/*/div - finds all <div> elements that are 4 level down
    • //*/div/a[@id='someIdValue'] - finds <a> (anchor/link) element (3rd level), under <div> (2nd level)
    • //input[@id='email'] - finds <input id='email' ...> field
    • //*[@id='unique_id'] - finds all/any tags with <sometag id='unique_id' ...>
    • //input[@type='submit' and @value='Login'] - finds all <input type='submit' value='Login' ...> tags
    • //input[@type='text' or @class='special'] - finds all <input type='text' ...> and <input class='special' ... tags
    • //input[starts-with(@class,'tbl_')] - finds all <input class='tbl_XXXX' ... tags
    • //input[contains(@id,'name')] - finds all <input id="XXXXnameYYYY" ...> tags
    • //input[@*='name'] - finds all tags that contain name in their attribute(s)
  • Use FirePath to find XPath of the elements on the page
  • WebDriver uses browser’s native XPath capabilities, if available
  • Different browser WebDrivers treat XPath differently:
    • HtmlUnitDriver - lower-cased, native XPath support
    • InternetExplorerDriver - lower-cased, no native XPath support
    • FirefoxDriver - lower-cased, native XPath support
  • XPath might be slow(er) on some platforms and browsers (e.g. IE)
  • See the attached cheatsheet, e.g.
    • https://www.simple-talk.com/dotnet/.net-framework/xpath,-css,-dom-and-selenium-the-rosetta-stone/
  • See more examples, e.g.
    • http://www.w3schools.com/xpath/

JavaScript

WebElement element = (WebElement) ((JavaScriptExecutor) browser).executeScript("return $('.something')[0]");
  • Finds web elements using JavaScript libraries, e.g. JQuery

RefactoredShoppingCartTest.java
package com.example.selenium.lab04;

import java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;

import org.junit.After;
import org.junit.Assert;
import org.junit.Before;
import org.junit.Test;
import org.openqa.selenium.By;
import org.openqa.selenium.NoAlertPresentException;
import org.openqa.selenium.firefox.FirefoxDriver;

public class RefactoredShoppingCartTest {

    private FirefoxDriver browser;

    @Before
    public void setUp() throws Exception {
        browser = new FirefoxDriver();
        browser.manage().timeouts().implicitlyWait(60, TimeUnit.SECONDS);
    }

    @Test
    public void testShoppingCart() {

        // open shopping page in firefox
        browser.navigate().to("https://XXXX-YYYY-DDDD.spree.mx/");

        // click on the 'SHOP' link at the top navigation bar
        browser.findElement(By.cssSelector(".container > nav.columns.seven > #main-nav-bar > #shop-link > a[href='/products']")).click();

        // click on the image of the 'Ruby on Rails Tote', 1st product 1st row
        // browser.findElement(By.cssSelector("li #product_1 > div.product-image > a > img[alt='Ruby on Rails Tote']")).click();
        // browser.findElement(By.cssSelector("li #product_1 > div.product-image > a > img")).click();
        browser.findElement(By.cssSelector("img[alt='Ruby on Rails Tote']")).click();

        // click on the add to cart button
        browser.findElement(By.id("add-to-cart-button")).click();

        // click 'Continue Shopping' button
        browser.findElement(By.cssSelector(".continue.button.gray")).click();

        // click on 'Spree' link in the sidebar under 'Shop by Brand' section
        browser.findElement(By.xpath("//aside[@id='sidebar']//a[.='Spree']")).click();

        // click on the 'Spree Ringer T-Shirt' image
        // browser.findElement(By.cssSelector("li #product_10 > div.product-image > a > img[alt='Spree Ringer T-Shirt']")).click();
        browser.findElement(By.cssSelector("img[alt='Spree Ringer T-Shirt']")).click();

        // click on 'Add to Cart' button
        browser.findElement(By.id("add-to-cart-button")).click();

        // verify that the actual total after adding to shopping cart is $35.98
        // By.cssSelector(".cart-total>td:nth-child(2)>h5")
        Assert.assertEquals("$35.98", browser.findElement(By.xpath("//tr[@class='cart-total']/td[2]/h5")).getText());

        // click on 'Continue Shopping' button
        browser.findElement(By.cssSelector(".continue.button.gray")).click();

        // click on the image of the 'Ruby on Rails Tote', 1st product 1st row
        // browser.findElement(By.cssSelector("li #product_1 > div.product-image > a > img[alt='Ruby on Rails Tote']")).click();
        browser.findElement(By.cssSelector("img[alt='Ruby on Rails Tote']")).click();

        // click on 'Featured' under 'Look for Similar Items'
        // browser.findElement(By.linkText("Featured")).click();
        browser.findElement(By.cssSelector("#similar_items_by_taxon > li > a[href='/t/featured']")).click();

        // make sure checkbox '$15.00-$18.00' in 'Price Range' is selected
        if (!browser.findElement(By.id("Price_Range_$15.00_-_$18.00")).isSelected()) {
            browser.findElement(By.id("Price_Range_$15.00_-_$18.00")).click();
        }

        // click on 'Search' button
        // browser.findElement(By.name("button")).click();
        browser.findElement(By.cssSelector("#sidebar_products_search>button[type='submit']")).click();

        // click on 'Cart' button in top right corner
        browser.findElement(By.cssSelector("a.cart-info.full")).click();

        // verify that the actual total in cart after info page is $35.98
        // By.cssSelector(".cart-total>td:nth-child(2)>h5")
        Assert.assertEquals("$35.98", browser.findElement(By.xpath("//tr[@class='cart-total']/td[2]/h5")).getText());

    }

    @After
    public void tearDown() {
        browser.quit();
    }

    public static boolean isAlertPresent(FirefoxDriver wd) {
        try {
            wd.switchTo().alert();
            return true;
        } catch (NoAlertPresentException e) {
            return false;
        }
    }

}

Page Object Design Pattern

Page Object

  • Popular design pattern in test automation
  • Enhances test maintenance
  • Reduces code duplication
  • Makes tests more robust
  • Makes tests more readable
  • Page Object is a class that encapsulates finding objects and page interaction
  • Page Object acts as an interface to a page of application under test (AUT)
  • When UI changes, tests should not change, just the Page Object locators
  • Exposes WHAT tests (users) can do
  • Hides HOW to do these things

Page Factory

  • Used as support for Page Object classes
  • Initializes web elements, e.g. 
    ShopPage shopPage = PageFactory.initElements(browser,ShopPage.class)
  • Use @FindBy to define web elements, e.g. 
    @FindBy(css="a.cart-info.full")
private WebElement cartLink;
  • Use @CacheLookup to cache lookups (if not navigating away from the page)
  • Web elements are evaluated lazily (using dynamic proxies)

Best Practices

  • Define a separate Page Object class for each page
  • Public methods represent the services the page offers
  • Different results for the same action are modelled as different methods
  • Tests should only talk to Page Object classes
  • Page Object should only talk to WebDriver (i.e. browser)
  • Don’t expose internals of the page
  • Leverage OOP to define similar pages and share same functionality
  • Page Object doesn’t need to represent the entire page
  • Generally, stay away from making assertions in the pages, rather expose methods that return values you want to assert.
  • Watch out for duplicated code
  • Watch out for large PageObject classes

MyAssert.java
package com.example.selenium.lab06;

import org.junit.Assert;

public class MyAssert {

    public static void contains(String expectedSubstring, String actualString) {
        if (actualString == null) {
            String msg = String.format("expected to contain \"%s\" but got null.", expectedSubstring);
            Assert.fail(msg);
        }
        if (expectedSubstring == null) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("expectedString shouldn't be null");
        }
        if (!actualString.contains(expectedSubstring)) {
            String msg = String.format("expected to contain \"%s\" but got \"%s\".", expectedSubstring, actualString);
            Assert.fail(msg);
        }
    }

}

RefactoredWithPageObjectsShoppingCartTest.java
package com.example.selenium.lab06;

import java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;

import org.junit.After;
import org.junit.Before;
import org.junit.Test;
import org.openqa.selenium.NoAlertPresentException;
import org.openqa.selenium.firefox.FirefoxDriver;

public class RefactoredWithPageObjectsShoppingCartTest {

    FirefoxDriver browser;

    @Before
    public void setUp() throws Exception {
        browser = new FirefoxDriver();
        browser.manage().timeouts().implicitlyWait(60, TimeUnit.SECONDS);
    }

    @Test
    public void testShoppingCart() {
        HomePage homePage = HomePage.open(browser);
        ShopPage shopPage = homePage.clickOnShopLinkInTopNavigationBar();
        ProductPage totePage = shopPage.clickOnImageWithText("Ruby on Rails Tote");
        CartPage cartPage = totePage.addProductToCart();
        shopPage = cartPage.clickContinueShoppingButton();
        BrandPage spreePage = shopPage.clickOnSpreeLinkInSidebarUnderShopByBrandSection();
        ProductPage spreeRingerTshirtPage = spreePage.clickOnImageWithText("Spree Ringer T-Shirt");
        cartPage = spreeRingerTshirtPage.addProductToCart();
        MyAssert.contains("$35.98",cartPage.getTotal());
        shopPage = cartPage.clickContinueShoppingButton();
        totePage = shopPage.clickOnImageWithText("Ruby on Rails Tote");
        FeaturedPage featuredPage = totePage.clickOnFeaturedLink();
        featuredPage.checkPriceRange("Price_Range_$15.00_-_$18.00");
        featuredPage.clickOnSearchButton();
        cartPage = featuredPage.clickOnCartLink();
        MyAssert.contains("$35.98",cartPage.getTotal());
    }

    @After
    public void tearDown() {
        browser.quit();
    }

    public static boolean isAlertPresent(FirefoxDriver wd) {
        try {
            wd.switchTo().alert();
            return true;
        } catch (NoAlertPresentException e) {
            return false;
        }
    }

}

BrandPage.java
package com.example.selenium.lab07;

import java.util.regex.Pattern;

import org.openqa.selenium.By;
import org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver;

public class BrandPage extends HomePage {

    private static final Pattern[] VALID_URL_PATTERNS = {
        Pattern.compile("^https?://([^/]+)/t/brand/([^\\?]+)?(\\?.*)?$")
    };

    private WebDriver browser;

    public BrandPage(WebDriver browser) {
        super(browser);
        this.browser = browser;
        MyPages.assertValidUrl(browser, VALID_URL_PATTERNS);
    }

    public BrandPage checkPriceRange(String range) {
        // make sure checkbox '$15.00-$18.00' in 'Price Range' is selected
        if (!browser.findElement(By.id(range)).isSelected()) {
            browser.findElement(By.id(range)).click();
        }
        MyPages.animationPause();
        return this;
    }

    public BrandPage clickOnSearchButton() {
        // click on 'Search' button
        // browser.findElement(By.name("button")).click();
        browser.findElement(By.cssSelector("#sidebar_products_search>button[type='submit']")).click();
        MyPages.animationPause();
        return this;
    }

    public BrandPage selectPriceRangeUnder10() {
        return checkPriceRange("Price_Range_Under_$10.00");
    }

    public BrandPage selectPriceRange10to15() {
        return checkPriceRange("Price_Range_$10.00_-_$15.00");
    }

    public BrandPage selectPriceRange15to18() {
        return checkPriceRange("Price_Range_$15.00_-_$18.00");
    }

    public BrandPage selectPriceRange18to20() {
        return checkPriceRange("Price_Range_$18.00_-_$20.00");
    }

    public BrandPage selectPriceRange20orOver() {
        return checkPriceRange("Price_Range_$20.00_or_over");
    }

}
CartPage.java
package com.example.selenium.lab07;

import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;
import java.util.regex.Pattern;

import org.openqa.selenium.By;
import org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver;
import org.openqa.selenium.WebElement;

public class CartPage extends HomePage {

    private static final Pattern[] VALID_URL_PATTERNS = {
        Pattern.compile("^https?://([^/]+)/cart$")
    };

    private WebDriver browser;

    public CartPage(WebDriver browser) {
        super(browser);
        this.browser = browser;
        MyPages.assertValidUrl(browser, VALID_URL_PATTERNS);
    }

    public ShopPage clickContinueShoppingButton() {
        // click 'Continue Shopping' button
        browser.findElement(By.cssSelector(".continue.button.gray")).click();
        MyPages.animationPause();
        return new ShopPage(browser);
    }

    public String getTotal() {
        // get the cart total amount
        return browser.findElement(By.xpath("//tr[@class='cart-total']/td[2]/h5")).getText();
    }

    public List<String> getItemTitles() {
        List<String> result = new ArrayList<>();
        for ( WebElement element : browser.findElements(By.xpath("//tbody[@id='line_items']/tr/td[@class='cart-item-description']/h4/a"))) {
            result.add(element.getText());
        };
        return result;
    }

    public List<String> getItemPrices() {
        List<String> result = new ArrayList<>();
        for ( WebElement element : browser.findElements(By.xpath("//tbody[@id='line_items']/tr/td[@class='cart-item-price']"))) {
            result.add(element.getText().trim());
        };
        return result;
    }

    public List<String> getItemQuantities() {
        List<String> result = new ArrayList<>();
        for ( WebElement element : browser.findElements(By.xpath("//tbody[@id='line_items']/tr/td[@class='cart-item-quantity']/input"))) {
            result.add(element.getAttribute("value"));
        };
        return result;
    }

    public List<String> getItemSubtotals() {
        List<String> result = new ArrayList<>();
        for ( WebElement element : browser.findElements(By.xpath("//tbody[@id='line_items']/tr/td[@class='cart-item-total']"))) {
            result.add(element.getText().trim());
        };
        return result;
    }

}

HomePage.java
package com.example.selenium.lab07;

import java.util.regex.Pattern;

import org.openqa.selenium.By;
import org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver;

public class HomePage {

    private static final String URL_PREFIX = "https://XXXX-YYYY-DDDD.spree.mx/";

    private static final Pattern[] VALID_URL_PATTERNS = {
        Pattern.compile("^https?://([^/]+)")
    };

    private WebDriver browser;

    public HomePage(WebDriver browser) {
        this.browser = browser;
        if ( !browser.getCurrentUrl().startsWith(URL_PREFIX) ) {
            throw new IllegalStateException("Browser is on the wrong page.");
        }
    }

    public static HomePage open(WebDriver browser) {
        // open shopping page in firefox
        browser.navigate().to(URL_PREFIX);
        HomePage homePage = new HomePage(browser);
        MyPages.animationPause();
        MyPages.assertValidUrl(browser, VALID_URL_PATTERNS);
        return homePage;
    }

    public ShopPage clickOnShopLinkInTopNavigationBar() {
        // click on the 'SHOP' link at the top navigation bar
        browser.findElement(By.cssSelector(".container > nav.columns.seven > #main-nav-bar > #shop-link > a[href='/products']")).click();
        MyPages.animationPause();
        return new ShopPage(browser);
    }

    public ProductPage clickOnImageWithText(String alternateText) {
        // click on the image of the 'Ruby on Rails Tote', 1st product 1st row
        // browser.findElement(By.cssSelector("li #product_1 > div.product-image > a > img[alt='Ruby on Rails Tote']")).click();
        // browser.findElement(By.cssSelector("li #product_1 > div.product-image > a > img")).click();
        browser.findElement(MyBy.imageWithAltText(alternateText)).click();
        MyPages.animationPause();
        return new ProductPage(browser);
    }

    public CartPage clickOnCartLink() {
        // click on 'Cart' button in top right corner
        browser.findElement(By.cssSelector("a.cart-info.full")).click();
        MyPages.animationPause();
        return new CartPage(browser);
    }

}
MoreRefactoringWithPageObjectsShoppingCartTest.java
package com.example.selenium.lab07;

import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;

import org.junit.After;
import org.junit.Before;
import org.junit.Test;
import org.openqa.selenium.NoAlertPresentException;
import org.openqa.selenium.firefox.FirefoxDriver;

public class MoreRefactoringWithPageObjectsShoppingCartTest {

    private FirefoxDriver browser;

    @Before
    public void setUp() throws Exception {
        browser = new FirefoxDriver();
        browser.manage().timeouts().implicitlyWait(60, TimeUnit.SECONDS);
    }

    @Test
    public void testShoppingCart() {
        HomePage homePage = HomePage.open(browser);
        ShopPage shopPage = homePage.clickOnShopLinkInTopNavigationBar();
        ProductPage totePage = shopPage.clickOnImageWithText("Ruby on Rails Tote");
        CartPage cartPage = totePage.addProductToCart();
        shopPage = cartPage.clickContinueShoppingButton();
        BrandPage spreePage = shopPage.clickOnSpreeBrandSection();
        ProductPage spreeRingerTshirtPage = spreePage.clickOnImageWithText("Spree Ringer T-Shirt");
        cartPage = spreeRingerTshirtPage.addProductToCart();
        MyAssert.contains("$35.98",cartPage.getTotal());
        shopPage = cartPage.clickContinueShoppingButton();
        totePage = shopPage.clickOnImageWithText("Ruby on Rails Tote");
        FeaturedPage featuredPage = totePage.clickOnFeaturedLink().selectPriceRange15to18().clickOnSearchButton();
        cartPage = featuredPage.clickOnCartLink();
        MyAssert.contains("$35.98",cartPage.getTotal());
    }

    @Test
    public void testShoppingCartWithAnimationPause() {
        MyPages.setAnimationDelay(2.0);
        HomePage homePage = HomePage.open(browser);
        ShopPage shopPage = homePage.clickOnShopLinkInTopNavigationBar();
        ProductPage totePage = shopPage.clickOnImageWithText("Ruby on Rails Tote");
        CartPage cartPage = totePage.addProductToCart();
        shopPage = cartPage.clickContinueShoppingButton();
        BrandPage spreePage = shopPage.clickOnSpreeBrandSection();
        ProductPage spreeRingerTshirtPage = spreePage.clickOnImageWithText("Spree Ringer T-Shirt");
        cartPage = spreeRingerTshirtPage.addProductToCart();
        MyAssert.contains("$35.98",cartPage.getTotal());
        shopPage = cartPage.clickContinueShoppingButton();
        ProductPage spaghettiPage = shopPage.clickOnImageWithText("Spree Jr. Spaghetti");
        cartPage = spaghettiPage.addProductToCart();
        shopPage = cartPage.clickContinueShoppingButton();
        spaghettiPage = shopPage.clickOnImageWithText("Spree Jr. Spaghetti");
        cartPage = spaghettiPage.addProductToCart();
        MyAssert.listContains(Arrays.asList("Ruby on Rails Tote", "Spree Ringer T-Shirt", "Spree Jr. Spaghetti"), cartPage.getItemTitles());
        MyAssert.listContains(Arrays.asList("$15.99", "$19.99", "$19.99"), cartPage.getItemPrices());
        MyAssert.listContains(Arrays.asList("1", "1", "2"), cartPage.getItemQuantities());
        MyAssert.listContains(Arrays.asList("$15.99", "$19.99", "$39.98"), cartPage.getItemSubtotals());
        MyAssert.contains("$75.96",cartPage.getTotal());
    }

    @After
    public void tearDown() {
        browser.quit();
    }

    public static boolean isAlertPresent(FirefoxDriver wd) {
        try {
            wd.switchTo().alert();
            return true;
        } catch (NoAlertPresentException e) {
            return false;
        }
    }

}
MyAssert.java
package com.example.selenium.lab07;

import java.util.List;

import org.junit.Assert;

public class MyAssert {

    public static void contains(String expectedSubstring, String actualString) {

        if (actualString == null) {
            String msg = String.format("expected to contain \"%s\" but got null.", expectedSubstring);
            Assert.fail(msg);
        }
        if (expectedSubstring == null) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("expectedString shouldn't be null");
        }
        if (!actualString.contains(expectedSubstring)) {
            String msg = String.format("expected to contain \"%s\" but got \"%s\".", expectedSubstring, actualString);
            Assert.fail(msg);
        }

    }

    public static void listContains(List<String> expectedList, List<String> actualList) {
        if ( expectedList == null ) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("expectedList shouldn't be null");
        }
        if ( actualList == null ) {
            String msg = String.format("expected to contain \"%s\" elements but got null.", expectedList.size());
            Assert.fail(msg);
        }
        for(int i=0;i<expectedList.size(); i++) {
            String expectedSubstring = expectedList.get(i);
                try {
                String actualString = actualList.get(i);
                if ( !actualString.contains(expectedSubstring) ) {
                    String msg = String.format("expected to contain \"%s\" but got \"%s\".", expectedSubstring, actualString);
                    Assert.fail(msg);
                }
                } catch (IndexOutOfBoundsException e) {
                String msg = String.format("expected to retrieve element id=%s from actual list, but was not able to,", i);
                Assert.fail(msg);
            }
        }
    }

    public static void contains(String expectedSubstring, List<String> actualList) {
        if ( expectedSubstring == null ) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("expectedList shouldn't be null");
        }
        if ( actualList == null ) {
            String msg = String.format("expected to contain \"%s\" elements but got null.", expectedSubstring);
            Assert.fail(msg);
        }
        for (String actualString : actualList) {
            if ( actualString.contains(expectedSubstring) ) return;
        }
        String msg = String.format("expected substring is not a substring in \"%s\".", actualList);
        Assert.fail(msg);
    }

}

MyPages.java
package com.example.selenium.lab07;

import java.util.regex.Pattern;

import org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver;

public class MyPages {

    private static double animationDelay = 0.0;

    public static void animationPause() {
        double delay = animationDelay;
        MyWaits.sleep(delay);
    }

    public static void setAnimationDelay(double seconds) {
        animationDelay = seconds;
    }

    public static void assertValidUrl(WebDriver browser, Pattern[] validUrlPatterns) {
        String url = browser.getCurrentUrl();
        if (! isValidUrl(url, validUrlPatterns))
            throw new IllegalStateException("Browser is on the wrong page: " + url);
    }

    private static boolean isValidUrl(String url, Pattern[] validUrlPatterns) {
        for (Pattern pattern : validUrlPatterns) {
            if ( pattern.matcher(url).find()) {
                return true;
            }
        }
        return false;
    }

}
MyWaits.java
package com.example.selenium.lab07;

public class MyWaits {

    public static void sleep(double seconds) {
        long millis = (long) (1000L * seconds);
        try {
            Thread.sleep(millis);
        } catch (InterruptedException e) {
            Thread.currentThread().interrupt();
        }
    }

}

ShopPage.java
package com.example.selenium.lab07;

import java.util.regex.Pattern;

import org.openqa.selenium.By;
import org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver;

public class ShopPage extends HomePage {

    private static final Pattern[] VALID_URL_PATTERNS = {
        Pattern.compile("^https?://([^/]+)/products(\\?.*)?$"),
        Pattern.compile("^https?://([^/]+)/t/featured(\\?.*)?$"),
        Pattern.compile("^https?://([^/]+)/t/brand/([^/]+)(\\?.*)?$"),
        Pattern.compile("^https?://([^/]+)/t/categories/([^/+])(\\?.*)?$")
    };

    private WebDriver browser;

    public ShopPage(WebDriver browser) {
        super(browser);
        this.browser = browser;
        MyPages.assertValidUrl(browser, VALID_URL_PATTERNS);
    }

    public BrandPage clickOnRubyBrandSection() {
        return clickOnBrand("Ruby");
    }

    public BrandPage clickOnApacheBrandSection() {
        return clickOnBrand("Apache");
    }

    public BrandPage clickOnSpreeBrandSection() {
        return clickOnBrand("Spree");
    }

    public BrandPage clickOnRailsBrandSection() {
        return clickOnBrand("Rails");
    }

    public BrandPage clickOnBrand(String brandName) {
        // click on brand link in the sidebar under 'Shop by Brand' section
        browser.findElement(By.xpath("//aside[@id='sidebar']//a[.='" + brandName + "']")).click();
        return new BrandPage(browser);
    }

}

CartPage.java
package com.example.selenium.lab08;

import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;
import java.util.regex.Pattern;

import org.openqa.selenium.By;
import org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver;
import org.openqa.selenium.WebElement;
import org.openqa.selenium.support.FindBy;
import org.openqa.selenium.support.PageFactory;

public class CartPage extends HomePage {

    private static final Pattern[] VALID_URL_PATTERNS = {
        Pattern.compile("^https?://([^/]+)/cart$")
    };

    @FindBy(css=".continue.button.gray")
    private WebElement continueShoppingButton;

    @FindBy(xpath="//tr[@class='cart-total']/td[2]/h5")
    private WebElement totalAmount;

    private WebDriver browser;

    public CartPage(WebDriver browser) {
        super(browser);
        this.browser = browser;
        MyPages.assertValidUrl(browser, VALID_URL_PATTERNS);
    }

    public ShopPage clickContinueShoppingButton() {
        // click 'Continue Shopping' button
        continueShoppingButton.click();
        MyPages.animationPause();
        return PageFactory.initElements(browser, ShopPage.class);
    }

    public String getTotal() {
        // get the cart total amount
        return totalAmount.getText().trim();
    }

    public List<String> getItemTitles() {
        List<String> result = new ArrayList<>();
        for ( WebElement element : browser.findElements(By.xpath("//tbody[@id='line_items']/tr/td[@class='cart-item-description']/h4/a"))) {
            result.add(element.getText());
        };
        return result;
    }

    public List<String> getItemPrices() {
        List<String> result = new ArrayList<>();
        for ( WebElement element : browser.findElements(By.xpath("//tbody[@id='line_items']/tr/td[@class='cart-item-price']"))) {
            result.add(element.getText().trim());
        };
        return result;
    }

    public List<String> getItemQuantities() {
        List<String> result = new ArrayList<>();
        for ( WebElement element : browser.findElements(By.xpath("//tbody[@id='line_items']/tr/td[@class='cart-item-quantity']/input"))) {
            result.add(element.getAttribute("value"));
        };
        return result;
    }

    public List<String> getItemSubtotals() {
        List<String> result = new ArrayList<>();
        for ( WebElement element : browser.findElements(By.xpath("//tbody[@id='line_items']/tr/td[@class='cart-item-total']"))) {
            result.add(element.getText().trim());
        };
        return result;
    }

}

package com.example.selenium.lab08;

import java.util.regex.Pattern;

import org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver;
import org.openqa.selenium.WebElement;
import org.openqa.selenium.support.FindBy;
import org.openqa.selenium.support.PageFactory;

public class HomePage {

    private static final String URL_PREFIX = "https://XXXX-YYYY-DDDD.spree.mx/";

    private static final Pattern[] VALID_URL_PATTERNS = {
        Pattern.compile("^https?://([^/]+)")
    };

    @FindBy(css=".container > nav.columns.seven > #main-nav-bar > #shop-link > a[href='/products']")
    private WebElement shopLink;

    @FindBy(css="a.cart-info.full")
    private WebElement cartLink;

    private WebDriver browser;

    public HomePage(WebDriver browser) {
        this.browser = browser;
        if ( !browser.getCurrentUrl().startsWith(URL_PREFIX) ) {
            throw new IllegalStateException("Browser is on the wrong page.");
        }
    }

    public static HomePage open(WebDriver browser) {
        // open shopping page in firefox
        browser.navigate().to(URL_PREFIX);
        HomePage homePage = PageFactory.initElements(browser, HomePage.class);

        MyPages.assertValidUrl(browser, VALID_URL_PATTERNS);
        return homePage;
    }

        MyPages.animationPause();
        return PageFactory.initElements(browser, ShopPage.class);
    }

MyAssert.java
package com.example.selenium.lab08;

import java.util.List;

import org.junit.Assert;

public class MyAssert {

    public static void contains(String expectedSubstring, String actualString) {
        if (actualString == null) {
            String msg = String.format("expected to contain \"%s\" but got null.", expectedSubstring);
            Assert.fail(msg);
        }
        if (expectedSubstring == null) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("expectedString shouldn't be null");
        }
        if (!actualString.contains(expectedSubstring)) {
            String msg = String.format("expected to contain \"%s\" but got \"%s\".", expectedSubstring, actualString);
            Assert.fail(msg);
        }
    }

    public static void listContains(List<String> expectedList, List<String> actualList) {
        if ( expectedList == null ) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("expectedList shouldn't be null");
        }
        if ( actualList == null ) {
            String msg = String.format("expected to contain \"%s\" elements but got null.", expectedList.size());
            Assert.fail(msg);
        }
        for(int i=0;i<expectedList.size(); i++) {
            String expectedSubstring = expectedList.get(i);
                try {
                String actualString = actualList.get(i);
                if ( !actualString.contains(expectedSubstring) ) {
                    String msg = String.format("expected to contain \"%s\" but got \"%s\".", expectedSubstring, actualString);
                    Assert.fail(msg);
                }
                } catch (IndexOutOfBoundsException e) {
                String msg = String.format("expected to retrieve element id=%s from actual list, but was not able to,", i);
                Assert.fail(msg);
            }
        }
    }

    public static void contains(String expectedSubstring, List<String> actualList) {
        if ( expectedSubstring == null ) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("expectedList shouldn't be null");
        }
        if ( actualList == null ) {
            String msg = String.format("expected to contain \"%s\" elements but got null.", expectedSubstring);
            Assert.fail(msg);
        }
        for (String actualString : actualList) {
            if ( actualString.contains(expectedSubstring) ) return;
        }
        String msg = String.format("expected substring is not a substring in \"%s\".", actualList);
        Assert.fail(msg);
    }

}

MyPages.java
package com.example.selenium.lab08;

import java.util.regex.Pattern;

import org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver;

public class MyPages {

    private static double animationDelay = 0.0;

    public static void animationPause() {
        double delay = animationDelay;
        MyWaits.sleep(delay);
    }

    public static void setAnimationDelay(double seconds) {
        animationDelay = seconds;
    }

    public static void assertValidUrl(WebDriver browser, Pattern[] validUrlPatterns) {
        String url = browser.getCurrentUrl();
        if (! isValidUrl(url, validUrlPatterns))
            throw new IllegalStateException("Browser is on the wrong page: " + url);
    }

    private static boolean isValidUrl(String url, Pattern[] validUrlPatterns) {
        for (Pattern pattern : validUrlPatterns) {
            if ( pattern.matcher(url).find()) {
                return true;
            }
        }
        return false;
    }

}
MyWaits.java
package com.example.selenium.lab08;

public class MyWaits {

    public static void sleep(double seconds) {
        long millis = (long) (1000L * seconds);
        try {
            Thread.sleep(millis);
        } catch (InterruptedException e) {
            Thread.currentThread().interrupt();
        }
    }

}

RefactoringWithPageFactoryShoppingCartTest.java
package com.example.selenium.lab08;

import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;

import org.junit.After;
import org.junit.Before;
import org.junit.Test;
import org.openqa.selenium.NoAlertPresentException;
import org.openqa.selenium.firefox.FirefoxDriver;

public class RefactoringWithPageFactoryShoppingCartTest {

    private FirefoxDriver browser;

    @Before
    public void setUp() throws Exception {
        browser = new FirefoxDriver();
        browser.manage().timeouts().implicitlyWait(60, TimeUnit.SECONDS);
    }

    @Test
    public void testShoppingCart() {
        HomePage homePage = HomePage.open(browser);
        ShopPage shopPage = homePage.clickOnShopLinkInTopNavigationBar();
        ProductPage totePage = shopPage.clickOnImageWithText("Ruby on Rails Tote");
        CartPage cartPage = totePage.addProductToCart();
        shopPage = cartPage.clickContinueShoppingButton();
        BrandPage spreePage = shopPage.clickOnSpreeBrandSection();
        ProductPage spreeRingerTshirtPage = spreePage.clickOnImageWithText("Spree Ringer T-Shirt");
        cartPage = spreeRingerTshirtPage.addProductToCart();
        MyAssert.contains("$35.98",cartPage.getTotal());
        shopPage = cartPage.clickContinueShoppingButton();
        totePage = shopPage.clickOnImageWithText("Ruby on Rails Tote");
        FeaturedPage featuredPage = totePage.clickOnFeaturedLink().selectPriceRange15to18().clickOnSearchButton();
        cartPage = featuredPage.clickOnCartLink();
        MyAssert.contains("$35.98",cartPage.getTotal());
    }

    @Test
    public void testShoppingCartWithAnimationPause() {
        MyPages.setAnimationDelay(2.0);
        HomePage homePage = HomePage.open(browser);
        ShopPage shopPage = homePage.clickOnShopLinkInTopNavigationBar();
        ProductPage totePage = shopPage.clickOnImageWithText("Ruby on Rails Tote");
        CartPage cartPage = totePage.addProductToCart();
        shopPage = cartPage.clickContinueShoppingButton();
        BrandPage spreePage = shopPage.clickOnSpreeBrandSection();
        ProductPage spreeRingerTshirtPage = spreePage.clickOnImageWithText("Spree Ringer T-Shirt");
        cartPage = spreeRingerTshirtPage.addProductToCart();
        MyAssert.contains("$35.98",cartPage.getTotal());
        shopPage = cartPage.clickContinueShoppingButton();
        ProductPage spaghettiPage = shopPage.clickOnImageWithText("Spree Jr. Spaghetti");
        cartPage = spaghettiPage.addProductToCart();
        shopPage = cartPage.clickContinueShoppingButton();
        spaghettiPage = shopPage.clickOnImageWithText("Spree Jr. Spaghetti");
        cartPage = spaghettiPage.addProductToCart();
        MyAssert.listContains(Arrays.asList("Ruby on Rails Tote", "Spree Ringer T-Shirt", "Spree Jr. Spaghetti"), cartPage.getItemTitles());
        MyAssert.listContains(Arrays.asList("$15.99", "$19.99", "$19.99"), cartPage.getItemPrices());
        MyAssert.listContains(Arrays.asList("1", "1", "2"), cartPage.getItemQuantities());
        MyAssert.listContains(Arrays.asList("$15.99", "$19.99", "$39.98"), cartPage.getItemSubtotals());
        MyAssert.contains("$75.96",cartPage.getTotal());
    }

    @After
    public void tearDown() {
        browser.quit();
    }

    public static boolean isAlertPresent(FirefoxDriver wd) {
        try {
            wd.switchTo().alert();
            return true;
        } catch (NoAlertPresentException e) {
            return false;
        }
    }

}

Introduction to Cucumber

What is Cucumber?

  • Tool for running automated acceptance tests using Behaviour-Driven Development (BDD) / Gherkin style
  • Uses plain text to define feature documentation
  • There are few implementations, originally written in Ruby
  • Cucumber Site
    • http://cucumber.io

What is BDD?

  • Technique that encourages close collaboration between developers, QA, and business (non-technical) stakeholders in the project
  • Developed by Dan North as a response to TDD (Test-Driven Development) shortcomings
    • Where to start the process?
    • What to test and what not to test?
    • How much to test in one go?
    • What to call the tests?
    • How to understand why a test fails?
  • Unit test names should be whole sentences starting with word "Should" and should be written in order of business value.
  • Acceptance tests should be written as an Agile User Story, e.g. "As a [role] I want [feature] so that [benefit]."
  • Acceptance criteria should be written in terms of scenarios and implemented as classes, e.g. "Given [initial context], when [event occurs], then [ensure some outcomes]."

BDD Projects

  • JBehave (Java)
  • Concordion (Java)
  • Cucumber-Java (Java)
  • RBehave (Ruby - later integrated into RSpec)
  • Cucumber (Ruby)
  • Jasmine (Javascript)
  • Cucumber-js (Javascript)
  • Behave (Python)

Practices of BDD

  • Establish the shared goals for all stakeholders
  • Define features that will achieve these goals
  • Involve all stakeholders during the development process
  • Use examples to describe the behaviour of the application (user stories)
  • Automate examples for regression and immediate feedback
  • Use "should" when describing the behaviour of software
  • Use "ensure" when describing the responsibilities of software
  • Use mock objects as replacement for real code not written yet

Gherking Syntax (BDD Language)

  • Feature (required)
  • Background (optional)
  • Scenario (required)
  • Given (optional)
  • When (required)
  • Then (required)
  • Scenario Outline (optional)
  • Examples (required if scenario outline used)

Gherkin Example

Feature: Sign up

    Sign up should be quick and friendly.

    Scenario: Successful sign up

        New users should get a confirmation email and be greeted personally by the site once signed in.

        Given I have chosen to sign up
        When I sign up with valid details
        Then I should receive a confirmation email
        And I should see a personalized greeting message

    Scenario: Duplicate email

        Where someone tries to create an account for an email address that already exists.

        Given I have chosen to sign up
        When I sign up with an email address that has already registered
        Then I should be told that the email is already registered
        And I should be offered the option to recover my password

Suggested Workflow (simplified)

  • Get all stakeholders together, e.g. users, business analysts, developers, testers, product managers, etc.
  • They describe the behaviour of a new feature in plain text using Gherkin style.
  • Developers add feature files to the project and integrate into testing.
  • Run the tests, watch them fail, cucumber will output information for the glue/step code.
  • Developers write the code that will pass the first step (test).
  • Rinse and repeat until all steps (tests) are GREEN.

How do I configure Cucumber in Java?

  • Easiest using Maven, add dependencies for:
    • junit
    • cucumber-java
    • cucumber-junit
  • Edit your pom.xml, e.g. 
    <dependencies>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>junit</groupId>
        <artifactId>junit</artifactId>
        <version>${junit.version}</version>
        <scope>test</scope>
    </dependency>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>info.cukes</groupId>
        <artifactId>cucumber-java</artifactId>
        <version>${cucumber.version}</version>
        <scope>test</scope>
    </dependency>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>info.cukes</groupId>
        <artifactId>cucumber-junit</artifactId>
        <version>${cucumber.version}</version>
        <scope>test</scope>
    </dependency>
</dependencies>
  • Organize your test code, step definitions and features, e.g. 
    pom.xml

    package com.example.selenium.lab09;

import org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver;

public class ShoppingStepDefs {

    public void cleanup() {

                            .selectPriceRange20orOver()

                            .selectPriceRange18to20()
                            .clickOnSearchButton();
    }

        MyAssert.contains(expectedAmount, cart.getTotal());

BrandPage.java
package com.example.selenium.lab09;

import java.util.regex.Pattern;

import org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver;
import org.openqa.selenium.WebElement;
import org.openqa.selenium.support.FindBy;

public class BrandPage extends HomePage {

    private static final Pattern[] VALID_URL_PATTERNS = {
        Pattern.compile("^https?://([^/]+)/t/brand/([^\\?]+)?(\\?.*)?$")
    };

    @FindBy(css="#sidebar_products_search>button[type='submit']")
    private WebElement submitButton;

    @FindBy(id="Price_Range_Under_$10.00")
    private WebElement priceRangeUnder10;

    @FindBy(id="Price_Range_$10.00_-_$15.00")
    private WebElement priceRange10to15;

    @FindBy(id="Price_Range_$15.00_-_$18.00")
    private WebElement priceRange15to18;

    @FindBy(id="Price_Range_$18.00_-_$20.00")
    private WebElement priceRange18to20;

    @FindBy(id="Price_Range_$20.00_or_over")
    private WebElement priceRangeOver20;

    public BrandPage(WebDriver browser) {
        super(browser);
        MyPages.assertValidUrl(browser, VALID_URL_PATTERNS);
    }

    private BrandPage checkPriceRange(WebElement checkbox) {
        // make sure checkbox in 'Price Range' is selected
        if (!checkbox.isSelected()) {
            checkbox.click();
        }
        MyPages.animationPause();
        return this;
    }

    public BrandPage clickOnSearchButton() {
        // click on 'Search' button
        submitButton.click();
        MyPages.animationPause();
        return this;
    }

    public BrandPage selectPriceRangeUnder10() {
        return checkPriceRange(priceRangeUnder10);
    }

    public BrandPage selectPriceRange10to15() {
        return checkPriceRange(priceRange10to15);
    }

    public BrandPage selectPriceRange15to18() {
        return checkPriceRange(priceRange15to18);
    }

    public BrandPage selectPriceRange18to20() {
        return checkPriceRange(priceRange18to20);
    }

    public BrandPage selectPriceRange20orOver() {
        return checkPriceRange(priceRangeOver20);
    }

}
CartPage.java
package com.example.selenium.lab09;

import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;
import java.util.regex.Pattern;

import org.openqa.selenium.By;
import org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver;
import org.openqa.selenium.WebElement;
import org.openqa.selenium.support.FindBy;
import org.openqa.selenium.support.PageFactory;

public class CartPage extends HomePage {

    private static final Pattern[] VALID_URL_PATTERNS = {
        Pattern.compile("^https?://([^/]+)/cart$")
    };

    @FindBy(css=".continue.button.gray")
    private WebElement continueShoppingButton;

    @FindBy(xpath="//tr[@class='cart-total']/td[2]/h5")
    private WebElement totalAmount;

    private WebDriver browser;

    public CartPage(WebDriver browser) {
        super(browser);
        this.browser = browser;
        MyPages.assertValidUrl(browser, VALID_URL_PATTERNS);
    }

    public ShopPage clickContinueShoppingButton() {
        // click 'Continue Shopping' button
        continueShoppingButton.click();
        MyPages.animationPause();
        return PageFactory.initElements(browser, ShopPage.class);
    }

    public String getTotal() {
        // get the cart total amount
        return totalAmount.getText().trim();
    }

    public List<String> getItemTitles() {
        List<String> result = new ArrayList<>();
        for ( WebElement element : browser.findElements(By.xpath("//tbody[@id='line_items']/tr/td[@class='cart-item-description']/h4/a"))) {
            result.add(element.getText());
        };
        return result;
    }

    public List<String> getItemPrices() {
        List<String> result = new ArrayList<>();
        for ( WebElement element : browser.findElements(By.xpath("//tbody[@id='line_items']/tr/td[@class='cart-item-price']"))) {
            result.add(element.getText().trim());
        };
        return result;
    }

    public List<String> getItemQuantities() {
        List<String> result = new ArrayList<>();
        for ( WebElement element : browser.findElements(By.xpath("//tbody[@id='line_items']/tr/td[@class='cart-item-quantity']/input"))) {
            result.add(element.getAttribute("value"));
        };
        return result;
    }

    public List<String> getItemSubtotals() {
        List<String> result = new ArrayList<>();
        for ( WebElement element : browser.findElements(By.xpath("//tbody[@id='line_items']/tr/td[@class='cart-item-total']"))) {
            result.add(element.getText().trim());
        };
        return result;
    }

}
