HomePage.java
package com.example.selenium.lab09;

import java.util.regex.Pattern;

import org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver;
import org.openqa.selenium.WebElement;
import org.openqa.selenium.support.FindBy;
import org.openqa.selenium.support.PageFactory;

public class HomePage {

    private static final String URL_PREFIX = "https://XXXX-YYYY-DDDD.spree.mx/";

    private static final Pattern[] VALID_URL_PATTERNS = {
        Pattern.compile("^https?://([^/]+)")
    };

    @FindBy(css=".container > nav.columns.seven > #main-nav-bar > #shop-link > a[href='/products']")
    private WebElement shopLink;

    @FindBy(css="a.cart-info.full")
    private WebElement cartLink;

    private WebDriver browser;

    public HomePage(WebDriver browser) {
        this.browser = browser;
        if ( !browser.getCurrentUrl().startsWith(URL_PREFIX) ) {
            throw new IllegalStateException("Browser is on the wrong page.");
        }
    }

    public static HomePage open(WebDriver browser) {
        // open shopping page in firefox
        browser.navigate().to(URL_PREFIX);
        HomePage homePage = PageFactory.initElements(browser, HomePage.class);
        MyPages.animationPause();
        MyPages.assertValidUrl(browser, VALID_URL_PATTERNS);
        return homePage;
    }

    public ShopPage clickOnShopLinkInTopNavigationBar() {
        // click on the 'SHOP' link at the top navigation bar
        shopLink.click();
        MyPages.animationPause();
        return PageFactory.initElements(browser, ShopPage.class);
    }

    public ProductPage clickOnImageWithText(String alternateText) {
        // click on the image of the 'Ruby on Rails Tote', 1st product 1st row
        // browser.findElement(By.cssSelector("li #product_1 > div.product-image > a > img[alt='Ruby on Rails Tote']")).click();
        // browser.findElement(By.cssSelector("li #product_1 > div.product-image > a > img")).click();
        browser.findElement(MyBy.imageWithAltText(alternateText)).click();
        MyPages.animationPause();
        return PageFactory.initElements(browser, ProductPage.class);
    }

    public CartPage clickOnCartLink() {
        // click on 'Cart' button in top right corner
        cartLink.click();
        MyPages.animationPause();
        return PageFactory.initElements(browser, CartPage.class);
    }

}
MyAssert.java
package com.example.selenium.lab09;

import java.util.List;

import org.junit.Assert;

public class MyAssert {

    public static void contains(String expectedSubstring, String actualString) {
        if (actualString == null) {
            String msg = String.format("expected to contain \"%s\" but got null.", expectedSubstring);
            Assert.fail(msg);
        }
        if (expectedSubstring == null) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("expectedString shouldn't be null");
        }
        if (!actualString.contains(expectedSubstring)) {
            String msg = String.format("expected to contain \"%s\" but got \"%s\".", expectedSubstring, actualString);
            Assert.fail(msg);
        }
    }

    public static void listContains(List<String> expectedList, List<String> actualList) {
        if ( expectedList == null ) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("expectedList shouldn't be null");
        }
        if ( actualList == null ) {
            String msg = String.format("expected to contain \"%s\" elements but got null.", expectedList.size());
            Assert.fail(msg);
        }
        for(int i=0;i<expectedList.size(); i++) {
            String expectedSubstring = expectedList.get(i);
                try {
                String actualString = actualList.get(i);
                if ( !actualString.contains(expectedSubstring) ) {
                    String msg = String.format("expected to contain \"%s\" but got \"%s\".", expectedSubstring, actualString);
                    Assert.fail(msg);
                }
                } catch (IndexOutOfBoundsException e) {
                String msg = String.format("expected to retrieve element id=%s from actual list, but was not able to,", i);
                Assert.fail(msg);
            }
        }
    }

    public static void contains(String expectedSubstring, List<String> actualList) {
        if ( expectedSubstring == null ) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("expectedList shouldn't be null");
        }
        if ( actualList == null ) {
            String msg = String.format("expected to contain \"%s\" elements but got null.", expectedSubstring);
            Assert.fail(msg);
        }
        for (String actualString : actualList) {
            if ( actualString.contains(expectedSubstring) ) return;
        }
        String msg = String.format("expected substring is not a substring in \"%s\".", actualList);
        Assert.fail(msg);
    }

}

MyPages.java
package com.example.selenium.lab09;

import java.util.regex.Pattern;

import org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver;

public class MyPages {

    private static double animationDelay = 0.0;

    public static void animationPause() {
        double delay = animationDelay;
        MyWaits.sleep(delay);
    }

    public static void setAnimationDelay(double seconds) {
        animationDelay = seconds;
    }

    public static void assertValidUrl(WebDriver browser, Pattern[] validUrlPatterns) {
        String url = browser.getCurrentUrl();
        if (! isValidUrl(url, validUrlPatterns))
            throw new IllegalStateException("Browser is on the wrong page: " + url);
    }

    private static boolean isValidUrl(String url, Pattern[] validUrlPatterns) {
        for (Pattern pattern : validUrlPatterns) {
            if ( pattern.matcher(url).find()) {
                return true;
            }
        }
        return false;
    }

}
MyWaits.java
package com.example.selenium.lab09;

public class MyWaits {

    public static void sleep(double seconds) {
        long millis = (long) (1000L * seconds);
        try {
            Thread.sleep(millis);
        } catch (InterruptedException e) {
            Thread.currentThread().interrupt();
        }
    }

}

package com.example.selenium.lab09;

import org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver;
import org.openqa.selenium.firefox.FirefoxDriver;

import cucumber.api.java.After;
import cucumber.api.java.Before;
import cucumber.api.java.en.Given;
import cucumber.api.java.en.Then;
import cucumber.api.java.en.When;

public class ShoppingStepDefs {

    private WebDriver browser;
    private HomePage home;
    private ShopPage shop;
    private BrandPage railsItems;
    private BrandPage searchedProducts;
    private ProductPage tote;
    private CartPage cart;

    @Before
    public void initialize() {
        browser = new FirefoxDriver();
    }

    @After
    public void cleanup() {
        browser.quit();
    }

    @Given("^I am viewing rails items$")
    public void i_am_viewing_rails_items() {
        home = HomePage.open(browser);
        shop = home.clickOnShopLinkInTopNavigationBar();
        railsItems = shop.clickOnRailsBrandSection();
    }

    @Given("^Items are \\$(\\d+)\\.(\\d+) or over$")
    public void items_are_15_dollars_or_over(double dollars, double cents) {
        searchedProducts = railsItems
                            .selectPriceRange20orOver()
                            .selectPriceRange15to18()
                            .selectPriceRange18to20()
                            .clickOnSearchButton();
    }

    @When("^I choose \"([^\"]*)\"$")
    public void i_choose(String product) {
        tote = searchedProducts.clickOnImageWithText(product);
    }

    @Given("^I add it to the cart$")
    public void i_add_it_to_the_car() {
        cart = tote.addProductToCart();
    }

    @Then("^\"([^\"]*)\" is in my shopping cart$")
    public void is_in_my_shopping_cart(String product) {
        MyAssert.contains(product, cart.getItemTitles());
    }

    @Then("^Total amount in the cart is \\$(\\d+)\\.(\\d+)$")
    public void total_amount_in_the_cart_is_$(int dollars, int cents) throws Throwable {
        String expectedAmount = "$" + dollars + "." + cents;
        MyAssert.contains(expectedAmount, cart.getTotal());
    }

}

Feature: As a shopper, when I need to get a gift, then I can purchase

    Scenario: I'm in trouble with my wife, I need to buy an expensive gift

        Given  I am viewing rails items
          And  Items are $15.00 or over
         When  I choose "Ruby on Rails Tote"
          And  I add it to the cart
         Then  "Ruby on Rails Tote" is in my shopping cart
          And  Total amount in the cart is $15.99

    Scenario: I'm in trouble with my mother, I need to buy a bag

        Given  I am viewing rails items
          And  Items are $15.00 or over
         When  I choose "Ruby on Rails Bag"
          And  I add it to the cart
         Then  "Ruby on Rails Bag" is in my shopping cart
          And  Total amount in the cart is $22.99

Summary of Automated Web Testing using Selenium and Cucumber on Java

In this course, you learned how to design, develop, and maintain automated web tests using Selenium and Cucumber on Java.

You should now be able to independently:

  • Rapidly create initial test scripts using Selenium Builder.
  • Navigate the WebDriver API and online documentation, and identify relevant parts necessary to perform key tasks.
  • Maintain, debug and modify Selenium test scripts using the Selenium API.
  • Communicate using the core vocabulary and concepts essential to testing with Selenium.
  • Use Selenium Selectors to interact with and verify content in web pages.
  • Refactor scripts for maintainability using the Page Object design pattern.
  • Integrate tests with Cucumber to achieve Behavior Driven / Acceptance Test Driven Development (BDD/ATDD).
